{"heading":"Milk comes before meat in the Church—Men’s works will be tried by fire—The Saints are the temple of God, and if they are faithful, they will inherit all things.","number":3,"verseCount":23,"verses":[[1,["And I, brethren, could not speak unto you as unto spiritual, but as unto carnal, ",["even",["clarity-word"]]," as unto babes in Christ."]],[2,["I have fed you with ",["milk",["study-note-ref","a",[["Heb. 5:12 (11–14)","nt/heb/5.12"],"; ",["1 Pet. 2:2 (1–3)","nt/1-pet/2.2"],"; ",["D&C 19:22","dc-testament/dc/19.22"],"; ",["50:40","dc-testament/dc/50.40"],"."]]],", and not with meat: for hitherto ye were not able ",["to bear it,",["clarity-word"]]," neither yet now are ye able."]],[3,["For ye are yet ",["carnal",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Carnal Mind","tg/carnal-mind"],"; ",["Man, Natural, Not Spiritually Reborn","tg/man-natural-not-spiritually-reborn"],"."]]],": for whereas ",["there is",["clarity-word"]]," among you ",["envying",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Envy","tg/envy"],"."]]],", and ",["strife",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Strife","tg/strife"],"."]]],", and ",["divisions",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Apostasy of the Early Christian Church","tg/apostasy-of-the-early-christian-church"],"."]]],", are ye not carnal, and walk as men?"]],[4,["For while one saith, I am of Paul; and another, I ",["am",["clarity-word"]]," of Apollos; are ye not carnal?"]],[5,["Who then is Paul, and who ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," Apollos, but ",["ministers",["study-note-ref","a",["GR servants. ",["2 Cor. 3:6","nt/2-cor/3.6"],"."]]]," by whom ye believed, even as the Lord gave to every man?"]],[6,["I have ",["planted",["study-note-ref","a",[["John 4:37 (36–38)","nt/john/4.37"],"; ",["1 Cor. 9:1","nt/1-cor/9.1"],"."]]],", Apollos watered; but God ",["gave",["study-note-ref","b",["GR caused, gave growth."]]]," the ",["increase",["study-note-ref","c",[["Mark 4:27 (26–29)","nt/mark/4.27"],"."]]],"."]],[7,["So then neither is he that planteth any thing, neither he that watereth; but God that giveth the increase."]],[8,["Now he that planteth and he that watereth are one: and every man shall receive his own ",["reward",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Reward","tg/reward"],"; ",["Wages","tg/wages"],"."]]]," according to his own labour."]],[9,["For we are ",["labourers",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Cor. 6:1","nt/2-cor/6.1"],"."]]]," together with God: ye are God’s ",["husbandry",["study-note-ref","b",["GR cultivated field, farm."]]],", ",["ye are",["clarity-word"]]," God’s building."]],[10,["According to the ",["grace",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Grace","tg/grace"],"."]]]," of God which is given unto me, as a wise masterbuilder, I have laid the foundation, and another buildeth thereon. But let every man take heed how he buildeth thereupon."]],[11,["For other ",["foundation",["study-note-ref","a",[["Matt. 16:18","nt/matt/16.18"],"; ",["2 Ne. 4:30","bofm/2-ne/4.30"],". ",["TG Cornerstone","tg/cornerstone"],"."]]]," can no man lay than that is laid, which is Jesus Christ."]],[12,["Now if any man build upon this foundation gold, silver, precious stones, wood, hay, stubble;"]],[13,["Every man’s work shall be made manifest: for the day shall ",["",1442],"declare it, because it shall be revealed by fire; and the ",["fire",["study-note-ref","a",[["Mal. 3:2 (2–3)","ot/mal/3.2"],"."]]]," shall ",["try",["study-note-ref","b",["GR test, put to proof. ",["TG Test","tg/test"],"."]]]," every man’s work of what sort it is."]],[14,["If any man’s work abide which he hath built thereupon, he shall receive a reward."]],[15,["If any man’s work shall be burned, he shall suffer loss: but he himself ",["shall",["study-note-ref","a",["JST 1 Cor. 3:15 … may …"]]]," be saved; yet so as by fire."]],[16,["Know ye not that ye are the ",["temple",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Body, Sanctity of","tg/body-sanctity-of"],"; ",["Life, Sanctity of","tg/life-sanctity-of"],"; ",["Temple","tg/temple"],"."]]]," of God, and ",["that",["clarity-word"]]," the ",["Spirit",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG God, Spirit of","tg/god-spirit-of"],"."]]]," of God dwelleth ",["in",["study-note-ref","c",["GR in, within, among."]]]," you?"]],[17,["If any man ",["defile",["study-note-ref","a",["GR spoil, corrupt, deprave. ",["TG Cleanliness","tg/cleanliness"],"; ",["Filthiness","tg/filthiness"],"; ",["Holy Ghost, Loss of","tg/holy-ghost-loss-of"],"; ",["Pollution","tg/pollution"],"; ",["Sacrilege","tg/sacrilege"],"; ",["Uncleanness","tg/uncleanness"],"; ",["Word of Wisdom","tg/word-of-wisdom"],"."]]]," the temple of God, him shall God destroy; for the temple of God is ",["holy",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Holiness","tg/holiness"],"; ",["Sacred","tg/sacred"],"."]]],", which ",["temple",["clarity-word"]]," ye are."]],[18,["Let no man deceive himself. If any man among you ",["seemeth",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Boast","tg/boast"],"."]]]," to be wise in this world, let him become a ",["fool",["study-note-ref","b",[["2 Ne. 9:42 (42–43)","bofm/2-ne/9.42"],"."]]],", that he may be ",["wise",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Learn","tg/learn"],"."]]],"."]],[19,["For the ",["wisdom",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG God, Wisdom of","tg/god-wisdom-of"],"; ",["Knowledge","tg/knowledge"],"; ",["Wisdom","tg/wisdom"],"."]]]," of this ",["world",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG World","tg/world"],"; ",["Worldliness","tg/worldliness"],"."]]]," is ",["foolishness",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Foolishness","tg/foolishness"],"."]]]," with God. For it is written, He taketh the wise in their own ",["craftiness",["study-note-ref","d",["GR cunning, villainy."]]],"."]],[20,["And again, The Lord ",["knoweth",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG God, Omniscience of","tg/god-omniscience-of"],"."]]]," the thoughts of the wise, that they are ",["vain",["study-note-ref","b",["GR deceptive, fruitless."]]],"."]],[21,["Therefore let no man ",["glory",["study-note-ref","a",[["1 Cor. 5:6","nt/1-cor/5.6"],"; ",["D&C 76:61 (58–62)","dc-testament/dc/76.61"],"."]]]," in men. For all things are yours;"]],[22,["Whether ",["Paul",["study-note-ref","a",[["D&C 76:99","dc-testament/dc/76.99"],"."]]],", or Apollos, or Cephas, or the world, or life, or death, or things present, or things to come; ",["all",["study-note-ref","b",[["Luke 12:44","nt/luke/12.44"],"."]]]," are yours;"]],[23,["And ye are ",["Christ’s",["study-note-ref","a",[["2 Cor. 10:7","nt/2-cor/10.7"],"."]]],"; and Christ ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," God’s."]]],"volume":"nt"}